<h4>
    Three Objects
</h4>

<p>
    Get a piece of plastic, a piece of paper, and a piece of metal.
    Touch each one. Which is the coldest?
    If you said the piece of metal...you're wrong!
    Unless one has been recently heated or cooled, they all have the same temperature!
    but if, as is likely the case, they have been in the same room for awhile,
    all of them are in <strong>thermal equilibrium</strong>
</p>
<p>
    The reason the metal feels colder is that it is a better conductor of heat than other
    substances.
    It takes heat away from your hand more effectively,
    and thus feels cooler.
    But it is not actually colder!
</p>


